  <prompt>
    Add unit tests covering the three Wave 0 code-changing tasks (002, 003, 005). Specifically:

    (a) **DTO mapping (task 002)** — `SendCommunicationRequestMappingTests`:
    - Only `AttachmentDocumentIds` set (alias path): canonical list populated; deprecation warning logged.
    - Only `AttachmentDriveItemIds` set (canonical path): canonical list populated; no warning.
    - Both set: canonical wins; structured warning logged.
    - Neither set: canonical list empty / null per design; no warning.

    (b) **`Internet-Message-Id` capture (task 003)** — `CommunicationServiceMessageIdTests`:
    - Success path: Graph `SendMail` succeeds → resolver returns an id → `sprk_internetmessageid` is stamped on the `sprk_communication` record.
    - Retrieval failure path: resolver returns null → warning logged → send does NOT throw → `sprk_communication` record exists but `sprk_internetmessageid` is null.
    - Retrieval retry: resolver throws once → single backoff retry → retry succeeds → field stamped.

    (c) **Client error class (task 005)** — `sendCommunication.error.test.ts` (Jest):
    - Non-2xx response with ProblemDetails body → `SendCommunicationError` thrown with `status`, `code`, `detail`, `correlationId` populated.
    - Non-2xx response with non-JSON body → `SendCommunicationError` thrown with `status` populated; other fields undefined.
    - 2xx response → no throw; resolves normally.
    - Deprecation warning fires ONCE per session when `attachmentDocumentIds` is used.

    Per CLAUDE.md §10 bullet 6 + spec.md §5.5, this task closes the bff-extensions.md test-update obligation for tasks 002 + 003.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke test engineer. Authoritative on `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` (xUnit + Moq + FluentAssertions per existing convention) and `@spaarke/ui-components` Jest setup. Familiar with `.claude/constraints/testing.md` patterns + `.claude/patterns/testing/unit-test-structure.md`.
  </role>

